						<summary>

						<p>On a slab built into the floor of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi>, north of the Tyāgarāja shrine in the Tyāgarājasvāmin temple.</p>						

						<p>Sarfōjī-mahārāja. Śaka 1639: 1717 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription mentions the king's predecessor Sahajī-mahārāja and his predecessor Ēkōji-mahārāja. The details of date given <hi rend="italic">viz.</hi> Śaka 1639, Kali 4818, Hēvilambi, Chittirai 15, śu. 13, Friday, Hasta, regularly correspond to 1717 A.D., April 12, Friday.</p>						

						<p>It records the renovation (<hi rend="italic">ashṭābandhaṉam</hi>) of the shrine of Mahāśivaliṅgamwithin the temple of god Tyāgarāja-svāmin Valmīkaṉāthasvāmin, by Mahāmaṇḍa, lēśvara Sarapōśi (Sarfōji)-mahārāja. </p>						

						</summary>
